TITLE: State documents appear to indicate Uvalde Sheriff Nolasco has not completed active shooter training
SUMMARY: Uvalde County Sheriff Ruben Nolasco does not appear to have completed an active shooter training course, according to documents CNN obtained Monday from the Texas Commission on Law Enforcement, the regulatory agency for peace officers in Texas.

TITLE: Biden administration prepares for surge of migrants ahead of the forced end of a Trump-era border policy
SUMMARY: As administration officials considered a border proposal reminiscent of the Trump era this month, Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer called Ron Klain, President Joe Biden's chief of staff, with concerns, according to three sources with knowledge of the call.

TITLE: Bernard Arnault just became the world's richest person. So who is he?
SUMMARY: Bernard Arnault, the chairman of French luxury goods giant LVMH, has just become the first European to top Bloomberg's list of the world's richest people, relegating Elon Musk to second place.

TITLE: What to expect from the Fed meeting
SUMMARY: The Federal Reserve is expected to raise interest rates by half a point at the conclusion of its two-day policy meeting on Wednesday, an indication that the central bank is pulling back on its aggressive stance as signs begin to emerge that inflation may be easing.

TITLE: Binance withdrawals jump to $3 billion in 24 hours, research firm says
SUMMARY: Investors withdrew as much as $3 billion from Binance on Tuesday, according to blockchain analytics firm Nansen, as the world's largest cryptocurrency exchange confronted investor jitters amid a deluge of negative headlines about the industry.

TITLE: UPS Semi-truck goes off bridge, catches fire
A month after 4 students were killed, police have yet to name a suspect
SUMMARY: A month after the gruesome killings of four University of Idaho students in their off-campus home, authorities have yet to name a suspect or locate the murder weapon as hundreds of students take final exams before winter break.

TITLE: Breonna Taylor's boyfriend reaches $2 million settlement with City of Louisville
SUMMARY: Breonna Taylor's boyfriend, Kenneth Walker III, has reached a $2 million dollar settlement with the City of Louisville, resolving lawsuits Walker filed in response to "the unlawful police raid that led to Ms. Taylor's death," a news release from Walker's legal team says.

TITLE: University of Texas men's basketball head coach charged with felony assault
SUMMARY: University of Texas at Austin men's basketball head coach Chris Beard was arrested and charged with a third-degree felony assault on Monday.

TITLE: January 6 committee chairman: Final public meeting will be Monday and full report will come out December 21
SUMMARY: Rep. Bennie Thompson, the chairman of the House select committee investigating the January 6, 2021, insurrection, told reporters the committee will hold its final public meeting on Monday and that the panel's full report will come out December 21.

TITLE: Justice Department has tried to access GOP Rep. Scott Perry's text messages
SUMMARY: The Justice Department has tried to gain access to Republican Rep. Scott Perry's text messages as part of a criminal investigation into 2020 election interference, facing off with his lawyers in a secret court proceeding after seizing his phone, CNN observed at the courthouse and sources familiar with the investigation said.

TITLE: Recount reconfirms GOP Rep. Lauren Boebert's victory in Colorado's 3rd District
SUMMARY: A recount reconfirmed that GOP Rep. Lauren Boebert defeated Democrat Adam Frisch in Colorado's 3rd Congressional District, the Colorado secretary of state said this week.
